Ah, we had - we had names for all our marbles, I can't think of 'em now, but the big - the one as you - the big 'un we used to call talleys. Else ones we used to call some stonies, ones like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid943631 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6899672\charrsid15295486 That's out of a pop bottle isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6576513 MA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6899672\charrsid15295486 No. That's the sort they used to put in the kettles to keep the fur on.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid943631 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6899672\charrsid15295486 What did you call those ones with the spiral in the middle?
