We did generally call they talleys. We - we had the glassy 'uns with a - what goes in for talleys. But these sort - we used to call them stonies, because you could buy a few marbles made of putty or summat, and they'd break at time. But that won't break.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid943631 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6899672\charrsid15295486 Where did it come from?
